{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":975,"text":"In 1975, I met in Florence a professor, Carlo Pedretti,"},{"time":5047,"text":"my former professor of art history, and today"},{"time":8377,"text":"a world-renowned scholar of Leonardo da Vinci."},{"time":12563,"text":"Well, he asked me if I could find some technological way"},{"time":16534,"text":"to unfold a five-centuries-old mystery related to"},{"time":20322,"text":"a lost masterpiece by Leonardo da Vinci,"},{"time":23135,"text":"the \"Battle of Anghiari,\" which is supposed to be located"},{"time":25762,"text":"in the Hall of the 500 in Palazzo Vecchio, in Florence."},{"time":28708,"text":"Well, in the mid-'70s, there were not great opportunities"},{"time":31811,"text":"for a bioengineer like me, especially in Italy, and so"},{"time":35738,"text":"I decided, with some researchers from the United States"},{"time":39608,"text":"and the University of Florence, to start probing the murals"},{"time":43819,"text":"decorated by Vasari on the long walls of the Hall of the 500"},{"time":47938,"text":"searching for the lost Leonardo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50615,"text":"Unfortunately, at that time we did not know that"},{"time":54069,"text":"that was not exactly where we should be looking,"},{"time":58411,"text":"because we had to go much deeper in, and so the research"},{"time":62549,"text":"came to a halt, and it was only taken up in 2000"},{"time":66884,"text":"thanks to the interest and the enthusiasm of the Guinness family."},{"time":71115,"text":"Well, this time, we focused on trying to reconstruct"},{"time":74354,"text":"the way the Hall of the 500 was before the remodeling,"},{"time":77210,"text":"and the so-called Sala Grande, which was built in 1494,"},{"time":81015,"text":"and to find out the original doors, windows,"},{"time":83895,"text":"and in order to do that, we first created a 3D model,"},{"time":88654,"text":"and then, with thermography, we went on to discover"},{"time":91756,"text":"hidden windows. These are the original windows of the hall"},{"time":94987,"text":"of the Sala Grande. We also found out about the height"},{"time":98565,"text":"of the ceiling, and we managed to reconstruct, therefore,"},{"time":101878,"text":"all the layout of this original hall"},{"time":104526,"text":"the way it was before there came Vasari,"},{"time":108081,"text":"and restructured the whole thing,"},{"time":110676,"text":"including a staircase that was very important"},{"time":114012,"text":"in order to precisely place \"The Battle of Anghiari\""},{"time":118151,"text":"on a specific area of one of the two walls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122415,"text":"Well, we also learned that Vasari, who was commissioned"},{"time":125656,"text":"to remodel the Hall of the 500 between 1560 and 1574"},{"time":130144,"text":"by the Grand Duke Cosimo I of the Medici family,"},{"time":134476,"text":"we have at least two instances when he saved masterpieces"},{"time":137917,"text":"specifically by placing a brick wall in front of it"},{"time":141174,"text":"and leaving a small air gap."},{"time":143539,"text":"One that we [see] here, Masaccio, the church of Santa Maria Novella in Florence,"},{"time":147227,"text":"so we just said, well maybe, Visari has done something"},{"time":150345,"text":"like that in the case of this great work of art by Leonardo,"},{"time":153731,"text":"since he was a great admirer of Leonardo da Vinci."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156216,"text":"And so we built some very sophisticated radio antennas"},{"time":160723,"text":"just for probing both walls and searching for an air gap."},{"time":165951,"text":"And we did find many on the right panel of the east wall,"},{"time":170786,"text":"an air gap, and that's where"},{"time":173408,"text":"we believe \"The Battle of Anghiari,\""},{"time":174958,"text":"or at least the part that we know has been painted,"},{"time":176924,"text":"which is called \"The Fight for the Standard,\" should be located."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180252,"text":"Well, from there, unfortunately,"},{"time":183845,"text":"in 2004, the project"},{"time":186499,"text":"came to a halt. Many political reasons."},{"time":189646,"text":"So I decided to go back to my alma mater,"},{"time":191980,"text":"and, at the University of California, San Diego,"},{"time":194652,"text":"and I proposed to open up a research center"},{"time":197018,"text":"for engineering sciences for cultural heritage."},{"time":199830,"text":"And in 2007, we created CISA3 as a research center"},{"time":204353,"text":"for cultural heritage, specifically art, architecture"},{"time":207166,"text":"and archaeology. So students started to flow in,"},{"time":209929,"text":"and we started to build technologies, because that's"},{"time":212063,"text":"basically what we also needed in order to move forward"},{"time":214712,"text":"and go and do fieldwork."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217472,"text":"We came back in the Hall of the 500 in 2011,"},{"time":221870,"text":"and this time, with a great group of students,"},{"time":225501,"text":"and my colleague, Professor Falko Kuester,"},{"time":227941,"text":"who is now the director at CISA3, and we"},{"time":230643,"text":"came back just since we knew already where to look for"},{"time":234816,"text":"to find out if there was still something left."},{"time":237796,"text":"Well, we were confined though, limited, I should rather say,"},{"time":241929,"text":"for several reasons that it's not worth explaining,"},{"time":244926,"text":"to endoscopy only, of the many other options we had,"},{"time":248672,"text":"and with a 4mm camera attached to it,"},{"time":252467,"text":"we were successful in documenting and taking"},{"time":257256,"text":"some fragments of what it turns out to be"},{"time":262060,"text":"a reddish color, black color, and there is some"},{"time":265660,"text":"beige fragments that later on"},{"time":269057,"text":"we ran a much more sophisticated exams,"},{"time":272051,"text":"XRF, X-ray diffraction, and the results are very positive"},{"time":277291,"text":"so far. It seems to indicate that indeed"},{"time":279954,"text":"we have found some pigments, and since we know for sure"},{"time":283010,"text":"that no other artist has painted on that wall"},{"time":285311,"text":"before Vasari came in about 60 years later, well,"},{"time":288830,"text":"those pigments are therefore firmly related to mural painting"},{"time":291691,"text":"and most likely to Leonardo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294306,"text":"Well, we are searching for the highest and highly praised"},{"time":299129,"text":"work of art ever achieved by mankind."},{"time":302370,"text":"As a matter of fact, this is by far the most important"},{"time":305575,"text":"commission that Leonardo has ever had,"},{"time":308411,"text":"and for doing this great masterpiece, he was named"},{"time":313024,"text":"the number one artist influence at the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317829,"text":"I had also had the privilege since the last 37 years"},{"time":321436,"text":"to work on several masterpieces as you can see behind me,"},{"time":325096,"text":"but basically to do what? Well, to assess, for example,"},{"time":328167,"text":"the state of conservation. See here the face of the"},{"time":330723,"text":"Madonna of the Chair that when just shining a UV light on it"},{"time":335447,"text":"you suddenly see another, different lady,"},{"time":338135,"text":"aged lady, I should rather say."},{"time":340430,"text":"There is a lot of varnish still sitting there, several retouches,"},{"time":344019,"text":"and some over cleaning. It becomes very visible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346866,"text":"But also, technology has helped to write new pages"},{"time":350623,"text":"of our history, or at least to update pages of our histories."},{"time":353545,"text":"For example, the \"Lady with the Unicorn,\""},{"time":355683,"text":"another painting by Rafael, well, you see the unicorn."},{"time":358161,"text":"A lot has been said and written about the unicorn, but"},{"time":360633,"text":"if you take an X-ray of the unicorn, it becomes a puppy dog."},{"time":364310,"text":"And — (Laughter) — no problem, but, unfortunately,"},{"time":368669,"text":"continuing with the scientific examination of this painting"},{"time":371447,"text":"came out that Rafael did not paint the unicorn,"},{"time":374447,"text":"did not paint the puppy dog, actually left the painting"},{"time":377104,"text":"unfinished, so all this writing about the exotic symbol"},{"time":381840,"text":"of the unicorn — (Laughter) — unfortunately,"},{"time":384731,"text":"is not very reliable. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":387891,"text":"Well, also, authenticity. Just think for a moment"},{"time":390491,"text":"if science really could move in the field of authenticity"},{"time":394586,"text":"of works of art. There would be a cultural revolution"},{"time":397974,"text":"to say the least, but also, I would say, a market revolution,"},{"time":401135,"text":"let me add. Take this example:"},{"time":403527,"text":"Otto Marseus, nice painting, which is \"Still Life\""},{"time":407221,"text":"at the Pitti Gallery, and just have an infrared camera peering through,"},{"time":411316,"text":"and luckily for art historians, it just was confirmed"},{"time":415051,"text":"that there is a signature of Otto Marseus. It even says"},{"time":417651,"text":"when it was made and also the location."},{"time":420666,"text":"So that was a good result. Sometimes, it's not that good,"},{"time":425065,"text":"and so, again, authenticity and science could go together"},{"time":430229,"text":"and change the way, not attributions being made,"},{"time":434526,"text":"but at least lay the ground for a more objective,"},{"time":438369,"text":"or, I should rather say, less subjective attribution,"},{"time":442090,"text":"as it is done today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444838,"text":"But I would say the discovery that really caught"},{"time":448132,"text":"my imagination, my admiration, is the incredibly vivid"},{"time":452239,"text":"drawing under this layer, brown layer,"},{"time":455851,"text":"of \"The Adoration of the Magi.\" Here you see"},{"time":459103,"text":"a handmade setting XYZ scanner with an infrared camera put on it,"},{"time":463533,"text":"and just peering through this brown layer"},{"time":466740,"text":"of this masterpiece to reveal"},{"time":469491,"text":"what could have been underneath."},{"time":472191,"text":"Well, this happens to be the most important painting"},{"time":474543,"text":"we have in Italy by Leonardo da Vinci, and"},{"time":477400,"text":"look at the wonderful images of faces that nobody has seen"},{"time":482136,"text":"for five centuries. Look at these portraits."},{"time":485827,"text":"They're magnificent. You see Leonardo at work."},{"time":488200,"text":"You see the geniality of his creation, right directly"},{"time":491857,"text":"on the ground layer of the panel, and see"},{"time":494764,"text":"this cool thing, finding, I should rather say,"},{"time":500836,"text":"an elephant. (Laughter) Because of this elephant,"},{"time":504098,"text":"over 70 new images came out, never seen for centuries."},{"time":507867,"text":"This was an epiphany. We came to understand"},{"time":511197,"text":"and to prove that the brown coating that we see today"},{"time":514923,"text":"was not done by Leonardo da Vinci, which left us"},{"time":517690,"text":"only the other drawing that for five centuries"},{"time":520197,"text":"we were not able to see, so thanks only to technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525407,"text":"Well, the tablet. Well, we thought, well, if we all have"},{"time":529783,"text":"this pleasure, this privilege to see all this,"},{"time":532561,"text":"to find all these discoveries, what about for everybody else?"},{"time":536099,"text":"So we thought of an augmented reality application"},{"time":538941,"text":"using a tablet. Let me show you just simulating"},{"time":543229,"text":"what we could be doing, any of us could be doing,"},{"time":546818,"text":"in a museum environment."},{"time":548993,"text":"So let's say that we go to a museum with a tablet, okay?"},{"time":553455,"text":"And we just aim the camera of the tablet"},{"time":556751,"text":"to the painting that we are interested to see, like this."},{"time":562882,"text":"Okay? And I will just click on it, we pause,"},{"time":568756,"text":"and now let me turn to you so the moment the image,"},{"time":572918,"text":"or, I should say, the camera, has locked in the painting,"},{"time":576271,"text":"then the images you just saw up there in the drawing"},{"time":578937,"text":"are being loaded. And so, see."},{"time":582694,"text":"We can, as we said, we can zoom in. Then we can scroll."},{"time":586497,"text":"Okay? Let's go and find the elephant."},{"time":591442,"text":"So all we need is one finger. Just wipe off"},{"time":594699,"text":"and we see the elephant. (Applause)"},{"time":599240,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":602784,"text":"Okay? And then if we want,"},{"time":605496,"text":"we can continue the scroll to find out, for example,"},{"time":608276,"text":"on the staircase, the whole iconography is going"},{"time":612371,"text":"to be changed. There are a lot of laymen reconstructing"},{"time":614699,"text":"from the ruins of an old temple a new temple,"},{"time":617330,"text":"and there are a lot of figures showing up. See?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621118,"text":"This is not just a curiosity, because it changes"},{"time":624324,"text":"not just the iconography as you see it, but the iconology,"},{"time":627372,"text":"the meaning of the painting,"},{"time":629723,"text":"and we believe this is a cool way, easy way,"},{"time":632513,"text":"that everybody could have access to, to become more"},{"time":635653,"text":"the protagonist of your own discovery, and not just"},{"time":638746,"text":"be so passive about it, as we are when we walk through"},{"time":642120,"text":"endless rooms of museums."},{"time":646314,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":651650,"text":"Another concept is the digital clinical chart, which sounds"},{"time":655407,"text":"very obvious if we were to talk about real patients,"},{"time":657882,"text":"but when we talk about works of art, unfortunately,"},{"time":660138,"text":"it's never been tapped as an idea."},{"time":662270,"text":"Well, we believe, again, that this should be the beginning,"},{"time":664825,"text":"the very first step, to do real conservation,"},{"time":667310,"text":"and allowing us to really explore and to understand"},{"time":670798,"text":"everything related to the state of our conservation,"},{"time":673589,"text":"the technique, materials, and also if, when, and why"},{"time":676963,"text":"we should restore, or, rather, to intervene on"},{"time":681554,"text":"the environment surrounding the painting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685085,"text":"Well, our vision is to rediscover"},{"time":688495,"text":"the spirit of the Renaissance, create a new discipline"},{"time":690904,"text":"where engineering for cultural heritage is actually"},{"time":694513,"text":"a symbol of blending art and science together."},{"time":697215,"text":"We definitely need a new breed of engineers"},{"time":699645,"text":"that will go out and do this kind of work and"},{"time":702378,"text":"rediscover for us these values, these cultural values"},{"time":706720,"text":"that we badly need, especially today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709274,"text":"And if you want to summarize in one just single word,"},{"time":713008,"text":"well, this is what we're trying to do."},{"time":715924,"text":"We're trying to give a future to our past"},{"time":718162,"text":"in order to have a future."},{"time":720564,"text":"As long as we live a life of curiosity and passion,"},{"time":723632,"text":"there is a bit of Leonardo in all of us. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":727818,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}